This paper is primarily focused on image classification and retrieval using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as support vector machines and k-nearest neighbors, which are commonly used in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to generating feature spaces using random convolutional blocks, which could be considered an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) topic. The use of random weights in the network also suggests a potential connection to the neural evolution (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the sensitivity of the network to background, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research.
